    "body": "> There's a meta-parent (0x00) that references all live root hashes of account tries. Previously on Clique and newly on post-merge mainnet too we can have 2 state tries have the same root, in which case we can have 2 references going from 0x00 to 0xchild. Dereferencing one should not dereference the other.\r\n\r\nI got it.\r\nAnother question, so does the item value of the children map represent only the child's reference count by the current node, rather than total reference count by all other nodes? I think so.",
